[SPEAKER_04]: It's mostly outside.

79
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:09,767
[SPEAKER_04]: Sometimes they have some spaces for inside tables.

80
00:06:10,647 --> 00:06:16,151
[SPEAKER_04]: I think they were actually doing a rain date this year rather than planning to move inside.

81
00:06:18,145 --> 00:06:26,373
[SPEAKER_04]: They are going to have food and DJs and Medford Brew Company and stuff like that.

82
00:06:26,393 --> 00:06:35,683
[SPEAKER_04]: If there's anybody who's never been, it is absolutely an entertaining Medford thing.

83
00:06:37,184 --> 00:06:42,207
[SPEAKER_04]: There is this Jingle Bell Festival, which is a fundraiser for the Buddy Colon Center.

84
00:06:42,267 --> 00:06:45,510
[SPEAKER_04]: So it's a center for people with Alzheimer's, a day center.

85
00:06:46,310 --> 00:06:53,615
[SPEAKER_04]: And they raffle off Christmas trees that are donated by the community.

86
00:06:53,936 --> 00:07:02,161
[SPEAKER_04]: And they have some wreaths and they have some other things that are a little less Christmassy, but it's truly a Christmas-based event.

87
00:07:02,942 --> 00:07:03,522
[SPEAKER_04]: And that

88
00:07:04,623 --> 00:07:12,004
[SPEAKER_04]: is kicked off that night, and then the mayor has developed sort of all this other stuff to go on at City Hall.

89
00:07:12,985 --> 00:07:19,646
[SPEAKER_04]: The trees are done by the private organization or the non-profit, and everything else is organized by the city.

90
00:07:21,906 --> 00:07:24,507
[SPEAKER_04]: But it is a sight to see, and they raise a lot.

91
00:07:24,547 --> 00:07:25,727
[SPEAKER_04]: It's their annual fundraiser.

92
00:07:26,107 --> 00:07:30,848
[SPEAKER_04]: They raise a lot of money, and it's when they turn on the lights outside City Hall.

