[SPEAKER_10]: We all agreed that, in thought before reading this, that maybe we should keep it, these are the, okay, so there's a couple of concerns.

732
01:06:58,302 --> 01:07:09,610
[SPEAKER_10]: One, maybe we should look at, of course, what they wrote, but try to keep it simple and concentrate more on trees that would be affected by construction.

733
01:07:09,690 --> 01:07:11,091
[SPEAKER_10]: And I asked them what they meant by that.

734
01:07:11,912 --> 01:07:24,278
[SPEAKER_10]: not just large site plan review construction, but all construction, because that would affect, or that does affect the most trees as far as having them removed.

735
01:07:25,559 --> 01:07:26,779
[SPEAKER_10]: So that was one thought.

736
01:07:26,799 --> 01:07:32,622
[SPEAKER_10]: The other thought was we have a lot of new city councilors that may be coming in or there's an election tomorrow.

737
01:07:33,647 --> 01:07:37,335
[SPEAKER_10]: And we don't know who's going to be on these committees with the city council.

738
01:07:37,836 --> 01:07:43,688
[SPEAKER_10]: So those people would need to be educated about, you know, trees and read also.

739
01:07:45,116 --> 01:07:46,877
[SPEAKER_10]: be appointed to that committee.

740
01:07:47,598 --> 01:07:48,979
[SPEAKER_10]: So that was a big question.

741
01:07:49,519 --> 01:08:00,027
[SPEAKER_10]: So one of the things that was brought up is that last year, late last year, through Planet Geo, there was a webinar for ordinances across the country.

742
01:08:01,027 --> 01:08:07,252
[SPEAKER_10]: What was done in a discussion, there was fantastic learning experience for all planners and

743
01:08:08,378 --> 01:08:10,760
[SPEAKER_10]: cities and people looking at tree ordinances.

744
01:08:11,420 --> 01:08:14,362
[SPEAKER_10]: And it was recorded and there was part one and part two.

745
01:08:14,962 --> 01:08:31,731
[SPEAKER_10]: So we agreed it would be a good idea to send it out to people just as education of what is out there already and also the difficulties other cities had for the guest speakers that are on that webinar and some key takeaways.

746
01:08:31,891 --> 01:08:35,954
[SPEAKER_10]: So I did send that email out too last week.

747
01:08:37,709 --> 01:08:53,720
[SPEAKER_10]: to the Energy Committee, but the other thought was also to send it to the city councilors that are on this Committee of the Whole too, at least to the future ones that may be appointed, which we don't know who they will be.

748
01:08:54,201 --> 01:08:56,863
[SPEAKER_10]: So we're losing, I think, three city councilors.

749
01:08:57,463 --> 01:09:05,449
[SPEAKER_04]: To be clear, just one thing, Loretta, the Committee of the Whole, whole means everybody, so all city councilors are on the Committee of the Whole.

750
01:09:07,258 --> 01:09:11,300
[SPEAKER_04]: Oh, so whoever gets elected tomorrow will be on it.

751
01:09:13,841 --> 01:09:17,203
[SPEAKER_10]: OK, so what about that subcommittee that actually reviews?

752
01:09:18,283 --> 01:09:22,745
[SPEAKER_04]: So sometimes things go to like a subcommittee on ordinances, things like that.

753
01:09:24,446 --> 01:09:28,068
[SPEAKER_04]: Sometimes they go to subcommittees and those you don't know who will be on it.

754
01:09:29,811 --> 01:09:42,777
[SPEAKER_04]: But I wouldn't worry too much about who, after tomorrow, I wouldn't worry so much about who educate them all, because in the end, all the city councilors have to vote on the ordinance, regardless of whether it's in subcommittee or committee.

755
01:09:44,598 --> 01:09:45,199
[SPEAKER_10]: Oh, I see.

756
01:09:45,499 --> 01:09:50,681
[SPEAKER_10]: So the meeting last month was the committee of the whole, but there were many members missing.

757
01:09:51,501 --> 01:09:53,702
[SPEAKER_10]: So that's why I thought it was the subcommittee.

758
01:09:54,423 --> 01:09:54,703
[SPEAKER_04]: Yeah.

759
01:09:55,378 --> 01:09:57,900
[SPEAKER_10]: There was very, a lot of them were missing from the meeting.

760
01:09:58,160 --> 01:09:59,041
[SPEAKER_10]: So, okay.

761
01:10:00,162 --> 01:10:00,923
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay.

762
01:10:00,943 --> 01:10:02,544
[SPEAKER_04]: I think it was a committee of the whole.

763
01:10:03,925 --> 01:10:11,331
[SPEAKER_10]: That's what I was, in the past, when they were breaking the draft ordinance from Therese Medford up, they had it in a subcommittee.

764
01:10:12,112 --> 01:10:14,253
[SPEAKER_10]: So things, it's been, like I said, it's been a year.

765
01:10:14,974 --> 01:10:21,319
[SPEAKER_10]: So our job is to, you know, read, read the,

766
01:10:22,742 --> 01:10:26,905
