01:11:23,119 --> 01:11:24,761
[SPEAKER_07]: Well, she's got that version.

783
01:11:25,521 --> 01:11:26,903
[SPEAKER_07]: I hope to read it tomorrow.

784
01:11:29,585 --> 01:11:32,368
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay, so I didn't see that.

785
01:11:32,848 --> 01:11:34,149
[SPEAKER_10]: I was on the computer a lot today.

786
01:11:34,169 --> 01:11:35,470
[SPEAKER_10]: I didn't see that come through.

787
01:11:35,490 --> 01:11:39,754
[SPEAKER_10]: I'm curious what happened to the November 14th meeting they said.

788
01:11:42,397 --> 01:11:42,637
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay.

789
01:11:43,665 --> 01:11:55,927
[SPEAKER_10]: But anyway, so we thought it would be a good idea if we could collaborate and agree on some of this, but so we have a united front suggestion.

790
01:11:56,647 --> 01:12:10,530
[SPEAKER_07]: If the rest of the committee wants to delegate me and Loretta as a subcommittee that can act in the name of the Energy and Environment Committee,

791
01:12:12,538 --> 01:12:16,039
[SPEAKER_06]: You run into open meeting law questions, problems if you do that.

792
01:12:16,700 --> 01:12:28,443
[SPEAKER_06]: You and Loretta can just work on it and make a recommendation informally like Luke and I are working on solar roofs and make a recommendation to the, without being designated a subcommittee.

793
01:12:28,663 --> 01:12:36,366
[SPEAKER_04]: I think that the question is if they need to provide feedback to the city council before the next energy committee meeting,

794
01:12:37,480 --> 01:12:40,041
[SPEAKER_04]: do you all empower them to do that?

795
01:12:40,061 --> 01:12:49,385
[SPEAKER_04]: Or does this committee's feedback to the city council need to wait until you can discuss it at your next energy committee meeting?

796
01:12:50,785 --> 01:12:51,926
[SPEAKER_06]: I think it needs to wait.

797
01:12:52,666 --> 01:12:53,626
[SPEAKER_10]: It needs to wait.

798
01:12:54,947 --> 01:13:00,769
[SPEAKER_10]: I'm not ready to, and I'd like Luke to, I mean, he left early, but he's familiar with a lot of this.

799
01:13:00,849 --> 01:13:02,710
[SPEAKER_10]: So I'd like to see if he can,

800
01:13:05,123 --> 01:13:07,544
[SPEAKER_10]: So I'm unclear of how do we proceed?

801
01:13:07,884 --> 01:13:21,569
[SPEAKER_10]: What is the suggestions of, I like what Barry said, we have, so actually getting back to what Barry said, we should do this on our own and submit our comments to the committee at the next meeting.

802
01:13:21,589 --> 01:13:25,970
[SPEAKER_03]: That would make sense.

803
01:13:26,110 --> 01:13:34,233
[SPEAKER_03]: Alicia, do we have any sense of when the city council expects the review to occur by all these groups that were provided the drafts?

804
01:13:35,475 --> 01:13:39,696
