805
01:13:39,716 --> 01:13:41,056
[SPEAKER_10]: I did.

806
01:13:41,276 --> 01:13:43,597
[SPEAKER_10]: I did ask Alicia and Bob.

807
01:13:44,697 --> 01:13:52,039
[SPEAKER_10]: I met with Zach and I asked him, I said, does this need to be done in the next few weeks, you know, by the December or November?

808
01:13:52,559 --> 01:13:55,420
[SPEAKER_10]: And he said, I don't think we're going to get to it before the end of the year.

809
01:13:56,000 --> 01:13:58,601
[SPEAKER_10]: He said there's too much in with the elections and everything.

810
01:13:59,741 --> 01:14:00,401
[SPEAKER_10]: That's what he said.

811
01:14:00,541 --> 01:14:03,962
[SPEAKER_10]: So I think they're looking at the end of December, January, but.

812
01:14:04,682 --> 01:14:07,744
[SPEAKER_10]: It doesn't mean we should stall, but, you know.

813
01:14:08,224 --> 01:14:10,466
[SPEAKER_06]: We might be better off that way, actually.

814
01:14:10,486 --> 01:14:17,631
[SPEAKER_06]: You know, the city council is going to change, and I think it's going to change in our favor.

815
01:14:17,651 --> 01:14:18,311
[SPEAKER_10]: Right.

816
01:14:18,832 --> 01:14:19,712
[SPEAKER_10]: That's what I'm thinking.

817
01:14:21,594 --> 01:14:27,218
[SPEAKER_10]: Bob, let's get direction here.

818
01:14:27,238 --> 01:14:33,202
[SPEAKER_10]: So we're going to read it and comment on our own and submit

