[SPEAKER_10]: They might require them to keep a certain percentage on the property.

1082
01:40:49,373 --> 01:41:13,877
[SPEAKER_10]: But if it was 300 inches of trees removed in diameter of the trunk, they could pay that amount, whatever the fee is per inch, to the city and they put this burden back on the city to plant that amount of trees, whatever that would buy, if trees are $200 each for small trees or whatever, to plant them somewhere else on public property.

