01:42:34,693 --> 01:42:42,736
[SPEAKER_06]: but there's three particular things that, actually there were four, but I'm gonna skip one of them that I'm concerned about.

1100
01:42:42,956 --> 01:42:49,578
[SPEAKER_06]: One was, there was some really problematic language in the original ordinance regarding affordable housing.

1101
01:42:49,898 --> 01:42:54,159
[SPEAKER_06]: And I hope that that has been dealt with.

1102
01:42:54,880 --> 01:42:59,081
[SPEAKER_06]: The second thing is what Dan is alluding to,

1103
01:43:00,140 --> 01:43:04,241
[SPEAKER_06]: is that there was no exclusion for invasive and noxious species.

1104
01:43:04,642 --> 01:43:09,183
[SPEAKER_06]: And I hope that that has been addressed.

1105
01:43:10,583 --> 01:43:16,885
[SPEAKER_06]: And the third, which I suspect has not been addressed, is the mitigation.

1106
01:43:17,686 --> 01:43:24,468
[SPEAKER_06]: And I suspect it's not been addressed because I'm even hearing people talking about inches now, diameter inches.

1107
01:43:25,237 --> 01:43:30,079
[SPEAKER_06]: And anybody here, I mean, there's a number of people here with engineering background and math background.

1108
01:43:30,619 --> 01:43:32,380
[SPEAKER_06]: Diameter isn't the right measure.

1109
01:43:33,601 --> 01:43:36,862
[SPEAKER_06]: Cross section, the area of cross section is the right measure.

1110
01:43:37,302 --> 01:43:43,505
[SPEAKER_06]: Three, four inch trees is nowhere near equivalent to a 12 inch diameter tree.

1111
01:43:44,225 --> 01:43:50,028
[SPEAKER_06]: It's like, that's like three baby trees compared to a big tree.

1112
01:43:52,036 --> 01:43:54,357
[SPEAKER_06]: So it shouldn't be measured in diameter.

1113
01:43:54,377 --> 01:43:56,757
[SPEAKER_06]: It should be measured in area of cross-section.

1114
01:43:57,937 --> 01:44:05,759
[SPEAKER_06]: That would be a lot closer to an accurate way to mitigate a loss of trees.

1115
01:44:08,839 --> 01:44:15,520
[SPEAKER_06]: And yeah, other comments are relatively minor, but those three are big.

